    {
      "id": "stvlQNzHPVqouGaKKc2cC",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 24913.084260217827,
      "y": 1689.3191880059892,
      "width": 954.71533203125,
      "height": 455,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b7H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1189136717,
      "version": 526,
      "versionNonce": 340791971,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1780053034190,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1) How can we ensure strong consistency for bids?\n    ❌ Row-level locking (SELECT ... FOR UPDATE)\n    ❌ Set default isolation level SERIALIZABLE for whole DB\n    ❌ Destributed lock\n            - needed when locks longer than db transaction\n            - high write throughput\n    ✅ Cache the max bid in memory (Redis)\n    ✅ ✅ Cache the max bid in database (add maxBidPrice)\n            1. Lock the auction row for the given auction (just one row)\n            2. Read the max bid for the given auction from the Auction table\n            3. Write the bid to the database with a status of accepted or rejected\n            4. Update the max bid in the Auction table if the new bid is higher\n            5. Commit the transaction",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1) How can we ensure strong consistency for bids?\n    ❌ Row-level locking (SELECT ... FOR UPDATE)\n    ❌ Set default isolation level SERIALIZABLE for whole DB\n    ❌ Destributed lock\n            - needed when locks longer than db transaction\n            - high write throughput\n    ✅ Cache the max bid in memory (Redis)\n    ✅ ✅ Cache the max bid in database (add maxBidPrice)\n            1. Lock the auction row for the given auction (just one row)\n            2. Read the max bid for the given auction from the Auction table\n            3. Write the bid to the database with a status of accepted or rejected\n            4. Update the max bid in the Auction table if the new bid is higher\n            5. Commit the transaction",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
