    {
      "id": "cvKFSw7ewInydSSo-m-T9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 27148.88887990541,
      "y": 1700.0088770702107,
      "width": 1410.6949462890625,
      "height": 280,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#228be6",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b7d",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1350908173,
      "version": 213,
      "versionNonce": 405605165,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1780053036708,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4) How can we ensure that the system scales to support 10M concurrent auctions?\n        ❌ Dispatcher service (Zookeper/etcd)\n        ✅ Pub-sub (Broadcasting)\n            - when Server A receives a new bid, it publishes that bid to the pub/sub system\n            - other instances of the Bid Service are subscribed to the same pub/sub channel and receive the message\n            - If the bid is for an auction that one of their current client connections is subscribed to\n            - they send that connection the new bid data.\n",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4) How can we ensure that the system scales to support 10M concurrent auctions?\n        ❌ Dispatcher service (Zookeper/etcd)\n        ✅ Pub-sub (Broadcasting)\n            - when Server A receives a new bid, it publishes that bid to the pub/sub system\n            - other instances of the Bid Service are subscribed to the same pub/sub channel and receive the message\n            - If the bid is for an auction that one of their current client connections is subscribed to\n            - they send that connection the new bid data.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
